    "In this, he joined <a href=\"/kimballf\">Fiske Kimball</a> and <a href=\"/edgellg\">George Harold Edgell</a> whose 1918 <em>History of Architecture</em> conceded the same point.": [],
    "He retired in 1930 and moved to Pulborough in Sussex where he designed personal buildings and domestic architecture.": [
